<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.49.7-8_0001a" />
   
<note type="curatorial"><del>130</del> 129 8-2-'66</note>

<opener>
<dateline>Aug. 2, '66,</dateline>

<salute>Dear Slade:</salute></opener> <p>Today I received copies of your Prayer Garden article in <hi rend="underline"><unclear/></hi>. It's a <hi rend="underline">bully</hi> article, and there's not one error in it! You will insist upon emphasizing my part in the article; but that <hi rend="underline">had</hi> to be so, <del>and</del><add>and</add> you organized the material for use in a most effective way.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.49.7-8_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
<fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

<p>On August 7th (next Sunday) the next "Neihardt Day' will be celebrated at Bancroft with the big <hi rend="underline">Black Elk</hi> pageant and Sioux Horse Dance. We are all going. I wish you and Nita were going to be there too. It is, I gather, <hi rend="double underline">quite</hi> an impressive presentation. (90 people in it)</p>

<p>Did I write you about my two <note type="authorial">(over)</note>

<fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.49.7-8_0002"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

weeks at Wayne State? It was bully! Did I tell you of the new bust and of plans for Homecoming on Oct. 14?</p>
<closer>
<salute>Love to you and Nita.</salute>

&#8212; <signed>John N.</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

